b'Old Mutual are proud partners of @wemovethenation, even more so now as @kabelomabalane and @petenikuzwayo have reached their destination today following a gruelling 600 km 17-day \xe2\x80\x9cHope With Every Step\xe2\x80\x9d run from Johannesburg to Durban. All to raise hope and funds to help reduce hunger and malnutrition of our nations children.\n\nYou can still play your part by contributing on www.hopewitheverystep.com'

b'Just over 2 weeks ago, the small steps being taken to achieve great things began with #HopeWithEveryStep, to raise R6 million to feed 10 000 children. We are now at the final stretch as our messengers of hope @wemovethenation near the finishing line. We are calling on as much support as we can get. Take a look and be inspired to be a part of the solution too. #RunWithHope #TheTimeIsNow\n\nVisit: www.hopewitheverystep.com to play your part.'

b'Staying on track while you try to achieve your goal can be difficult. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we are challenging you to take part in our #RunWithHope initiative by running in solidarity with @wemovethenation and donating to help raise R6 million to feed 10 000 children. Share an image of yourself after your run using #RunWithHope and #HopeWithEveryStep #TheTimeIsNow\n\nVisit: www.hopewitheverystep.com to play your part.'

b'The power of running is that every step you take gets you closer to achieving your goal. Move The Nation \xe2\x80\x93 a social running movement, powered by Old Mutual began their run from Johannesburg to Durban to raise R6 million to feed 10000 kids for a year. #RunWithHope #RunningReimagined #TheTimeIsNow \n\nVisit: www.hopewitheverystep.com to donate'
b'No two people are the same. So why should their cover be? Introducing Old Mutual #PersonalCover that\xe2\x80\x99s tailored just for you. \n\nClick the link on our bio to learn more.'

b'Mikaela Krone joined Old Mutual as a graduate early last year, but even in that short time she has been amazed by the big dynamic shifts happening in the work culture. What resonates mostly with Mikaela is that we give back to the communities we serve and we care and support the people around us. #175Africa'

b'Kayembe Gilles Ilunga is one of Old Mutual\xe2\x80\x99s young executives based in the Southern African Development Community (SADC). Since he joined the company six years ago, Gilles\xe2\x80\x99s positive opinion of the company\xe2\x80\x99s vision and values has continued to grow. A highlight of Gilles\xe2\x80\x99s role is that he gets to travel across Africa on business experiencing different cultures and meeting different people who inspire him to do great things everyday. #175africa'

b'Gideon is a legend at Old Mutual. Since joining Old Mutual 40 years ago, he\xe2\x80\x99s been awarded the Chairman\xe2\x80\x99s prize for being the No 1 Financial Adviser 34 times consecutively. #175Africa'

b'We recognise that our 175yrs of success is only possible because of the many amazing people who do great things every day. Marshall is a proverbial giant who  reminds us that while things change, our commitment to our customers\xe2\x80\x99 dreams is timeless. #175Africa'
b'We are committed to increase financial literacy rates in Africa and invest in a better future for Africa\xe2\x80\x99s children. #175Africa'
b'Our digital classroom allows us to invest in schools and teachers to drive innovation and results for Africa\xe2\x80\x99s children. #175Africa'
b'We are building financial education programmes to reach millions across the African continent. #175Africa'
b'We are investing in a better future across Africa. #175Africa'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s our 175th birthday and we are building Africa\xe2\x80\x99s biggest digital classroom. This initiative will change the way we learn forever. #175Africa'
